McGraw-Hill Board Authorizes Buyback of Up to 50 Million Shares

-- B y   O l i v e r   S t a l e y
-- 
2011-06-29T14:03:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/mcgraw-hill-board-authorizes-buyback-of-up-to-50-million-shares.html
The McGraw-Hill Co., the publisher
and provider of financial data, said it will buy back up to 50
million shares, or 17 percent of its outstanding stock, to
increase shareholder value.  McGraw-Hill rose 9 cents to $40.65 at 10:01 in New York
Stock Exchange composite trading. Shares of the New York-based
publisher have climbed 12 percent this year.  The company announced the buyback program in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oliver Staley in New York at 
 ostaley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Kaufman at 
 jkaufman17@bloomberg.net  